    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"actionable\" sounds like you're saying we should prioritize cutting these programs to fix the labor market. if the disincentive argument is the most \"clear\" one, does that mean the other factors like automation or the shift in work-life balance priorities are just secondary or less important to consider in actual policy making?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
